task.summary: Default task
SudokuEval implemented
Added a 'addNumbers' to the Graphics Interface.
Changed the hardcoded column/row size to take in a grid dimension size to be more dynamic.
Connected the backend grid to the coordinate grid in the graphics interface.
Removed the evaluator that comes with the brute force algorithm object.
Changed the column/row size to take into account index of 9 (instead of 0-8 only for 9x9 grid. We want to keep track of 9s too right?).
Changed hard-coded random generator to cap at the size of the grid dimension instead of 9.
Unsuccessful coding of 'trial and error' brute force.
Added some print statements.
Fiddled arounded with Random Generators.
Made various methods private. Users shouldn't be changing the UI of Sudoku.
Changed Evaluator to just take a 2d grid. Telling the AI what a subgrid is is still a challenge. TODO: implement subgrid.
Added new method that checks 2d subgrid in n^2 time.
Added a test to check whether checkAllSubgrids() works as it should.
Commented method
Run brute force.
Successfully implemented array copy
Now runs until 1,000,000 runs, and uses the same base grid without reference.
Changed to take the lower bound for "easy"
